----------------------------------------------------------------------
8. TIER 2.1 — FORCE LAW DERIVATION (COMPLETED)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Definition:
  Force measured as time-averaged momentum transfer:

      ⟨F⟩ = ΔP / Δt

Measurements performed:
  • Force vs EM amplitude A
  • Force vs EM frequency ω
  • Force vs impact parameter (offset)
  • Long-time averaging to remove oscillatory components


----------------------------------------------------------------------
9. TIER 2.1 RESULTS — FORCE VS AMPLITUDE
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Observed:
  • ⟨F⟩ extremely small (10⁻¹⁹–10⁻¹⁸ scale)
  • ⟨F⟩ approximately constant across A
  • No monotonic dependence on A
  • No A² scaling
  • Occasional sign changes
  • Frequent near-zero values

Ruled out conclusively:
  ✘ Radiation pressure
  ✘ F ∝ EM energy
  ✘ F ∝ A² (intensity)
  ✘ Classical momentum flux force


----------------------------------------------------------------------
10. TIER 2.1 RESULTS — FORCE VS FREQUENCY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Observed:
  • ⟨F⟩ varies with ω at fixed amplitude
  • Sign flips occur as ω is varied
  • Zeros appear at specific ω
  • Peaks and troughs present

Conclusion:
  • Force is frequency-dependent
  • Interaction is phase-sensitive
  • Momentum transfer depends on wave structure, not energy


----------------------------------------------------------------------
11. TIER 2.1 RESULTS — FORCE VS OFFSET
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Observed:
  • Near-zero force at symmetric impact
  • Finite force at large offsets
  • Sign consistent with geometric asymmetry
  • No classical cross-section profile

Conclusion:
  • Force arises from geometric asymmetry
  • Not from direct energy deposition


----------------------------------------------------------------------
12. FINAL TIER 2.1 PHYSICAL STATEMENT
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Tier 2.1 (Force Law — Completed):

In Motion–TimeSpace, electromagnetic interactions with solitons do not
produce a classical radiation force. Momentum transfer is small,
frequency-dependent, phase-sensitive, and controlled by geometric
interference with soliton structure rather than electromagnetic energy
flux.

This is a NEGATIVE LAW and a VALID RESULT.


